messages.content:
This is a missed-optimization in InstCombine.

The following program reveals the missed optimization.
The source program is
```llvm
define i8 @scmp_from_select_ne_const_and_gt_commuted1(i32 %x) {
  %ne = icmp ne i32 %x, 5
  %gt = icmp sgt i32 %x, 4
  %sel1 = select i1 %gt, i8 1, i8 -1
  %r = select i1 %ne, i8 %sel1, i8 0
  ret i8 %r
}

```

However, current LLVM cannot optimize the source program. The expected optimized program is
```llvm
define i8 @scmp_from_select_ne_const_and_gt_commuted1(i32 %x) {
  %r = call i8 @llvm.scmp.i8.i32(i32 %x, i32 5)
  ret i8 %r
}

; Function Attrs: nocallback nosync nounwind speculatable willreturn memory(none)
declare range(i8 -1, 2) i8 @llvm.scmp.i8.i32(i32, i32) #0

attributes #0 = { nocallback nosync nounwind speculatable willreturn memory(none) }

```
Please modify the following code in llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineSelect.cpp:InstCombinerImpl::foldSelectToCmp to implement the missed optimization:
